<TITLE> HC orders order bail in defamation case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 08 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Thursday ordered National Press Club president Shawkat Mahmud to surrender to the lower courts in three defamation suits. A High Court bench of justices Md Wahhab Mia and Md Abdur Razzak issued the order whilst rejecting Shawkat's bail petition. The court, however, asked the lower court to consider his bail petition. On Mar 20, Press Club president Shawkat Mahmud, a member of the BNP chairperson's advisory body, reportedly said at a meeting in Cox's Bazar that the state minister for law, Qamrul Islam was like "a lawyer under a banyan tree". Mahmud was referring at the time to a recent statement made by the state minister that action would be taken against those who still claim that BNP's founder Ziaur Rahman is the first person who declared independence of Bangladesh. The High Court last year ruled that Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, not Ziaur Rahman, was the 'declarer of independence'. b
